<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[869,1494,410,595]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,994,410,435]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Type data:</emphasis>
This variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moure et al." authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Perty" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1168,1399,410,435]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocnemis">
<emphasis box="[1168,1399,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Centris xanthocnemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a single male specimen collected in “Jundiahy” (= Jundiaí), southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1285,1345,474,499]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1360,1482,474,499]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="3.[94,153,2106,2131]" captionTargetBox="[94,1414,1585,2076]" captionTargetId="figure-27@3.[94,1417,1585,2076]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 3. Centrisxanthocnemis var.perflava Schrottky,1902 (holotype male).(A) Head,frontal view (scale bar:2 mm).(B) Habitus,dorsal view (scale bar:5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614966" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614966/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 3A, B</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[916,1017,506,531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
is housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1162,1226,506,531]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="Museum">MZSP</collectionCode>
and it has the following data label: 97262 [printed]\ 1376 [handwritten]\ [red label without text].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[869,1494,634,851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,1004,634,659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Comments:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[1063,1113,634,659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
specimen was caught by the insect collector Max Beron. It is a male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moure et al." authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Perty" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1316,1494,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocnemis">
<emphasis box="[1316,1494,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C. xanthocnemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with yellow pubescence on the mesosoma and hind legs instead of the blackish hairs found in most males. According to the accession book at MZSP the number 1,376 refers to the following data: “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1293,1357,794,819]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1373,1490,794,819]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, Jundiaí, M. Beron col” (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos, K. S. &amp; Kawada, R. &amp; Brandao, C. R." box="[1116,1319,826,851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="335 - 361" refId="ref4707" refString="Ramos, K. S.; Kawada, R. &amp; Brandao, C. R. 2015. Type specimens of bees (Hymenoptera, Apidae) deposited in the Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Brazil. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 55 (24): 335 - 361. DOI" type="journal article" year="2015">
Ramos 
<emphasis box="[1198,1255,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.,</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
